itemDescription: British naval officer of the Royal Navy

wikipedia_page.main: Admiral of the Fleet Sir Charles Edward Lambe,  (20 December 1900 – 29 August 1960) was a senior Royal Navy officer. He fought in the Second World War in command of a cruiser, as Director of Naval Plans and then in command of an aircraft carrier. He served as First Sea Lord and Chief of the Naval Staff from 1959 until 1960 when he was forced to retire early because of a heart condition. He died only a few months later.
